                        n
                    }
                }
            }()
              , i = {
                version: 0,
                hash: {
                    directionalLength: -1,
                    pointLength: -1,
                    spotLength: -1,
                    rectAreaLength: -1,
                    hemiLength: -1,

                    numLightProbes: -1

                ambient: [0, 0, 0],
                probe: [],

                numSpotLightShadowsWithMaps: 0,

            for (let t = 0; t < 9; t++)
                i.probe.push(new dp);
            const r = new dp
              , a = new zp
              , s = new zp;
            return {
                setup: function(r) {
                    let a = 0
                      , s = 0
                      , o = 0;
                    for (let t = 0; t < 9; t++)
                        i.probe[t].set(0, 0, 0);
                    let l = 0
                      , c = 0
                      , u = 0
                      , h = 0
                      , d = 0
                      , p = 0
                      , f = 0
                      , m = 0
                      , g = 0
                      , _ = 0
                      , v = 0;
                    r.sort(Av);
                    for (let t = 0, x = r.length; t < x; t++) {
                        const x = r[t]
                          , y = x.color
                          , S = x.intensity
                          , b = x.distance
                          , M = x.shadow && x.shadow.map ? x.shadow.map.texture : null;
                        if (x.isAmbientLight)
                            a += y.r * S,
                            s += y.g * S,
                            o += y.b * S;
                        else if (x.isLightProbe) {
                            for (let t = 0; t < 9; t++)
                                i.probe[t].addScaledVector(x.sh.coefficients[t], S);
                            v++
                        } else if (x.isDirectionalLight) {
                            const t = e.get(x);
                            if (t.color.copy(x.color).multiplyScalar(x.intensity),
                            x.castShadow) {
                                const t = x.shadow
                                  , e = n.get(x);
                                e.shadowIntensity = t.intensity,
                                e.shadowBias = t.bias,
                                e.shadowNormalBias = t.normalBias,
                                e.shadowRadius = t.radius,
                                e.shadowMapSize = t.mapSize,
                                i.directionalShadow[l] = e,
                                i.directionalShadowMap[l] = M,
                                i.directionalShadowMatrix[l] = x.shadow.matrix,
                                p++
                            }
                            i.directional[l] = t,
                            l++
                        } else if (x.isSpotLight) {
                            const t = e.get(x);
                            t.position.setFromMatrixPosition(x.matrixWorld),
                            t.color.copy(y).multiplyScalar(S),
                            t.distance = b,
                            t.coneCos = Math.cos(x.angle),
                            t.penumbraCos = Math.cos(x.angle * (1 - x.penumbra)),
                            t.decay = x.decay,
                            i.spot[u] = t;
                            const r = x.shadow;
                            if (x.map && (i.spotLightMap[g] = x.map,
                            g++,
                            r.updateMatrices(x),
                            x.castShadow && _++),
                            i.spotLightMatrix[u] = r.matrix,
                            x.castShadow) {
                                const t = n.get(x);
                                t.shadowIntensity = r.intensity,
                                t.shadowBias = r.bias,
                                t.shadowNormalBias = r.normalBias,
                                t.shadowRadius = r.radius,
                                t.shadowMapSize = r.mapSize,
                                i.spotShadow[u] = t,
                                i.spotShadowMap[u] = M,
                                m++
                            }
                            u++
                        } else if (x.isRectAreaLight) {
                            const t = e.get(x);
                            t.color.copy(y).multiplyScalar(S),
                            t.halfWidth.set(.5 * x.width, 0, 0),
                            t.halfHeight.set(0, .5 * x.height, 0),
                            i.rectArea[h] = t,
                            h++
                        } else if (x.isPointLight) {
                            const t = e.get(x);
                            if (t.color.copy(x.color).multiplyScalar(x.intensity),
                            t.distance = x.distance,
                            t.decay = x.decay,
                            x.castShadow) {
                                const t = x.shadow
                                  , e = n.get(x);
                                e.shadowIntensity = t.intensity,
                                e.shadowBias = t.bias,
                                e.shadowNormalBias = t.normalBias,
                                e.shadowRadius = t.radius,
                                e.shadowMapSize = t.mapSize,
                                e.shadowCameraNear = t.camera.near,
                                e.shadowCameraFar = t.camera.far,
                                i.pointShadow[c] = e,
                                i.pointShadowMap[c] = M,
                                i.pointShadowMatrix[c] = x.shadow.matrix,
                                f++
                            }
                            i.point[c] = t,
                            c++
                        } else if (x.isHemisphereLight) {
                            const t = e.get(x);
                            t.skyColor.copy(x.color).multiplyScalar(S),
                            t.groundColor.copy(x.groundColor).multiplyScalar(S),
                            i.hemi[d] = t,
                            d++
                        }
                    }
                    h > 0 && (!0 === t.has("OES_texture_float_linear") ? (i.rectAreaLTC1 = Qm.LTC_FLOAT_1,
                    i.rectAreaLTC2 = Qm.LTC_FLOAT_2) : (i.rectAreaLTC1 = Qm.LTC_HALF_1,
                    i.rectAreaLTC2 = Qm.LTC_HALF_2)),

                    VSM_SAMPLES: 8
                },

                        value: null
                    },

                        value: new up
                    },
                    radius: {
                        value: 4
                    }
                },
                vertexShader: "\nvoid main() {\n\n\tgl_Position = vec4( position, 1.0 );\n\n}\n",
                fragmentShader: "\nuniform sampler2D shadow_pass;\nuniform vec2 resolution;\nuniform float radius;\n\n#include <packing>\n\nvoid main() {\n\n\tconst float samples = float( VSM_SAMPLES );\n\n\tfloat mean = 0.0;\n\tfloat squared_mean = 0.0;\n\n\tfloat uvStride = samples <= 1.0 ? 0.0 : 2.0 / ( samples - 1.0 );\n\tfloat uvStart = samples <= 1.0 ? 0.0 : - 1.0;\n\tfor ( float i = 0.0; i < samples; i ++ ) {\n\n\t\tfloat uvOffset = uvStart + i * uvStride;\n\n\t\t#ifdef HORIZONTAL_PASS\n\n\t\t\tvec2 distribution = unpackRGBATo2Half( texture2D( shadow_pass, ( gl_FragCoord.xy + vec2( uvOffset, 0.0 ) * radius ) / resolution ) );\n\t\t\tmean += distribution.x;\n\t\t\tsquared_mean += distribution.y * distribution.y + distribution.x * distribution.x;\n\n\t\t#else\n\n\t\t\tfloat depth = unpackRGBAToDepth( texture2D( shadow_pass, ( gl_FragCoord.xy + vec2( 0.0, uvOffset ) * radius ) / resolution ) );\n\t\t\tmean += depth;\n\t\t\tsquared_mean += depth * depth;\n\n\t\t#endif\n\n\t}\n\n\tmean = mean / samples;\n\tsquared_mean = squared_mean / samples;\n\n\tfloat std_dev = sqrt( squared_mean - mean * mean );\n\n\tgl_FragColor = pack2HalfToRGBA( vec2( mean, std_dev ) );\n\n}\n"
            })

        function Nv(t, e, n, i) {
            const r = function(t) {
                switch (t) {
                case qh:
                case 1010:
                    return {
                        byteLength: 1,
                        components: 1
                    };
                case Yh:
                case 1011:
                case Jh:
                    return {
                        byteLength: 2,
                        components: 1
                    };
                case Qh:
                case td:
                    return {
                        byteLength: 2,
                        components: 4
                    };
                case Kh:
                case $h:
                case Zh:
                    return {
                        byteLength: 4,
                        components: 1
                    };
                case 35902:
                    return {
                        byteLength: 4,
                        components: 3
                    }
                }
                throw new Error(`Unknown texture type ${t}.`)
            }(i);
            switch (n) {
            case 1021:
                return t * e;
            case 1028:
            case ad:
                return t * e / r.components * r.byteLength;
            case 1030:
            case sd:
                return t * e * 2 / r.components * r.byteLength;
            case 1022:
                return t * e * 3 / r.components * r.byteLength;
            case nd:
            case od:
                return t * e * 4 / r.components * r.byteLength;
            case ld:
            case cd:
                return Math.floor((t + 3) / 4) * Math.floor((e + 3) / 4) * 8;
            case ud:
            case hd:
                return Math.floor((t + 3) / 4) * Math.floor((e + 3) / 4) * 16;
            case pd:
            case md:
                return Math.max(t, 16) * Math.max(e, 8) / 4;
            case dd:
            case fd:
                return Math.max(t, 8) * Math.max(e, 8) / 2;
            case gd:
            case _d:
                return Math.floor((t + 3) / 4) * Math.floor((e + 3) / 4) * 8;
            case vd:
            case xd:
                return Math.floor((t + 3) / 4) * Math.floor((e + 3) / 4) * 16;
            case yd:
                return Math.floor((t + 4) / 5) * Math.floor((e + 3) / 4) * 16;
            case Sd:
                return Math.floor((t + 4) / 5) * Math.floor((e + 4) / 5) * 16;
            case bd:
                return Math.floor((t + 5) / 6) * Math.floor((e + 4) / 5) * 16;
            case Md:
                return Math.floor((t + 5) / 6) * Math.floor((e + 5) / 6) * 16;
            case Ed:
                return Math.floor((t + 7) / 8) * Math.floor((e + 4) / 5) * 16;
            case Td:
                return Math.floor((t + 7) / 8) * Math.floor((e + 5) / 6) * 16;
            case wd:
                return Math.floor((t + 7) / 8) * Math.floor((e + 7) / 8) * 16;
            case Ad:
                return Math.floor((t + 9) / 10) * Math.floor((e + 4) / 5) * 16;
            case Rd:
                return Math.floor((t + 9) / 10) * Math.floor((e + 5) / 6) * 16;
            case Cd:
                return Math.floor((t + 9) / 10) * Math.floor((e + 7) / 8) * 16;
            case Pd:
                return Math.floor((t + 9) / 10) * Math.floor((e + 9) / 10) * 16;
            case Dd:
                return Math.floor((t + 11) / 12) * Math.floor((e + 9) / 10) * 16;
            case Ld:
                return Math.floor((t + 11) / 12) * Math.floor((e + 11) / 12) * 16;
            case Id:
            case Ud:
            case Od:
                return Math.ceil(t / 4) * Math.ceil(e / 4) * 16;
            case 36283:
            case Nd:
                return Math.ceil(t / 4) * Math.ceil(e / 4) * 8;
            case Fd:
            case Bd:
                return Math.ceil(t / 4) * Math.ceil(e / 4) * 16
            }
            throw new Error(`Unable to determine texture byte length for ${n} format.`)
        }

                null !== this._grip && this._grip.dispatchEvent(t),

            }
            connect(t) {
                if (t && t.hand) {
                    const e = this._hand;
                    if (e)
                        for (const n of t.hand.values())
                            this._getHandJoint(e, n)
                }

                    type: "connected",

                }),

            }
            disconnect(t) {

                    type: "disconnected",
                    data: t
                }),
                null !== this._targetRay && (this._targetRay.visible = !1),
                null !== this._grip && (this._grip.visible = !1),
                null !== this._hand && (this._hand.visible = !1),
                this
            }
            update(t, e, n) {

                  , r = null
                  , a = null;
                const s = this._targetRay
                  , o = this._grip
                  , l = this._hand;
                if (t && "visible-blurred" !== e.session.visibilityState) {
                    if (l && t.hand) {
                        a = !0;

                            const t = e.getJointPose(i, n)
                              , r = this._getHandJoint(l, i);

                            r.matrix.decompose(r.position, r.rotation, r.scale),
                            r.matrixWorldNeedsUpdate = !0,
                            r.jointRadius = t.radius),
                            r.visible = null !== t
                        }

                          , r = l.joints["thumb-tip"]

                          , o = .02

                        this.dispatchEvent({
                            type: "pinchend",
                            handedness: t.handedness,
                            target: this

        class Gv {
            constructor() {
                this.texture = null,
                this.mesh = null,
                this.depthNear = 0,
                this.depthFar = 0
            }
            init(t, e, n) {
                if (null === this.texture) {
                    const i = new Pp;
                    t.properties.get(i).__webglTexture = e.texture,
                    e.depthNear === n.depthNear && e.depthFar === n.depthFar || (this.depthNear = e.depthNear,
                    this.depthFar = e.depthFar),

                }
            }
            getMesh(t) {
                if (null !== this.texture && null === this.mesh) {
                    const e = t.cameras[0].viewport
                      , n = new mm({
                        vertexShader: "\nvoid main() {\n\n\tgl_Position = vec4( position, 1.0 );\n\n}",
                        fragmentShader: "\nuniform sampler2DArray depthColor;\nuniform float depthWidth;\nuniform float depthHeight;\n\nvoid main() {\n\n\tvec2 coord = vec2( gl_FragCoord.x / depthWidth, gl_FragCoord.y / depthHeight );\n\n\tif ( coord.x >= 1.0 ) {\n\n\t\tgl_FragDepth = texture( depthColor, vec3( coord.x - 1.0, coord.y, 1 ) ).r;\n\n\t} else {\n\n\t\tgl_FragDepth = texture( depthColor, vec3( coord.x, coord.y, 0 ) ).r;\n\n\t}\n\n}",
                        uniforms: {
                            depthColor: {
                                value: this.texture
                            },
                            depthWidth: {
                                value: e.z
                            },
                            depthHeight: {
                                value: e.w
                            }
                        }
                    });
                    this.mesh = new Km(new lm(20,20),n)
                }
                return this.mesh
            }
            reset() {
                this.texture = null,
                this.mesh = null
            }
            getDepthTexture() {
                return this.texture
            }
        }

        const Xv = new $p
          , jv = new zp;
        function qv(t, e) {
            function n(t, e) {

                        w.copy(t.viewport),

                        R = t.scissorTest
                    } else
                        w.copy(N).multiplyScalar(I).floor(),
                        A.copy(F).multiplyScalar(I).floor(),
                        R = B;

                    } else if (s) {

                          , r = e;
                        xt.framebufferTextureLayer(xt.FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, i.__webglTexture, n, r)
                    } else if (null !== t && 0 !== n) {

                this.readRenderTargetPixels = function(t, e, n, i, r, a, s, o=0) {
                    if (!t || !t.isWebGLRenderTarget)
                        return void console.error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixels: renderTarget is not THREE.WebGLRenderTarget.");
                    let l = Q.get(t).__webglFramebuffer;
                    if (t.isWebGLCubeRenderTarget && void 0 !== s && (l = l[s]),
                    l) {
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.FRAMEBUFFER, l);
                        try {
                            const s = t.textures[o]
                              , l = s.format
                              , c = s.type;
                            if (!K.textureFormatReadable(l))
                                return void console.error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixels: renderTarget is not in RGBA or implementation defined format.");
                            if (!K.textureTypeReadable(c))
                                return void console.error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixels: renderTarget is not in UnsignedByteType or implementation defined type.");
                            e >= 0 && e <= t.width - i && n >= 0 && n <= t.height - r && (t.textures.length > 1 && xt.readBuffer(xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + o),
                            xt.readPixels(e, n, i, r, gt.convert(l), gt.convert(c), a))
                        } finally {
                            const t = null !== M ? Q.get(M).__webglFramebuffer : null;
                            Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.FRAMEBUFFER, t)
                        }
                    }
                }
                ,
                this.readRenderTargetPixelsAsync = async function(t, e, n, i, r, a, s, o=0) {
                    if (!t || !t.isWebGLRenderTarget)
                        throw new Error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixels: renderTarget is not THREE.WebGLRenderTarget.");
                    let l = Q.get(t).__webglFramebuffer;
                    if (t.isWebGLCubeRenderTarget && void 0 !== s && (l = l[s]),
                    l) {
                        if (e >= 0 && e <= t.width - i && n >= 0 && n <= t.height - r) {
                            Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.FRAMEBUFFER, l);
                            const s = t.textures[o]
                              , c = s.format
                              , u = s.type;
                            if (!K.textureFormatReadable(c))
                                throw new Error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixelsAsync: renderTarget is not in RGBA or implementation defined format.");
                            if (!K.textureTypeReadable(u))
                                throw new Error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixelsAsync: renderTarget is not in UnsignedByteType or implementation defined type.");
                            const h = xt.createBuffer();
                            xt.bindBuffer(xt.PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER, h),
                            xt.bufferData(xt.PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER, a.byteLength, xt.STREAM_READ),
                            t.textures.length > 1 && xt.readBuffer(xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + o),
                            xt.readPixels(e, n, i, r, gt.convert(c), gt.convert(u), 0);
                            const d = null !== M ? Q.get(M).__webglFramebuffer : null;
                            Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.FRAMEBUFFER, d);
                            const p = xt.fenceSync(xt.SYNC_GPU_COMMANDS_COMPLETE, 0);
                            return xt.flush(),
                            await function(t, e) {
                                return new Promise((function(n, i) {
                                    setTimeout((function r() {
                                        switch (t.clientWaitSync(e, t.SYNC_FLUSH_COMMANDS_BIT, 0)) {
                                        case t.WAIT_FAILED:
                                            i();
                                            break;
                                        case t.TIMEOUT_EXPIRED:
                                            setTimeout(r, 4);
                                            break;
                                        default:
                                            n()
                                        }
                                    }
                                    ), 4)
                                }
                                ))
                            }(xt, p),
                            xt.bindBuffer(xt.PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER, h),
                            xt.getBufferSubData(xt.PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER, 0, a),
                            xt.deleteBuffer(h),
                            xt.deleteSync(p),
                            a
                        }
                        throw new Error("THREE.WebGLRenderer.readRenderTargetPixelsAsync: requested read bounds are out of range.")
                    }
                }

                this.copyFramebufferToTexture = function(t, e=null, n=0) {
                    const i = Math.pow(2, -n)
                      , r = Math.floor(t.image.width * i)
                      , a = Math.floor(t.image.height * i)
                      , s = null !== e ? e.x : 0
                      , o = null !== e ? e.y : 0;
                    tt.setTexture2D(t, 0),
                    xt.copyTexSubImage2D(xt.TEXTURE_2D, n, 0, 0, s, o, r, a),
                    Z.unbindTexture()
                }
                ;
                const Ht = xt.createFramebuffer()
                  , Vt = xt.createFramebuffer();
                this.copyTextureToTexture = function(t, e, n=null, i=null, r=0, a=null) {
                    let s, o, l, c, u, h, d, p, f;
                    null === a && (0 !== r ? (ih("WebGLRenderer: copyTextureToTexture function signature has changed to support src and dst mipmap levels."),
                    a = r,
                    r = 0) : a = 0);
                    const m = t.isCompressedTexture ? t.mipmaps[a] : t.image;
                    if (null !== n)
                        s = n.max.x - n.min.x,
                        o = n.max.y - n.min.y,
                        l = n.isBox3 ? n.max.z - n.min.z : 1,
                        c = n.min.x,
                        u = n.min.y,
                        h = n.isBox3 ? n.min.z : 0;
                    else {
                        const e = Math.pow(2, -r);
                        s = Math.floor(m.width * e),
                        o = Math.floor(m.height * e),
                        l = t.isDataArrayTexture ? m.depth : t.isData3DTexture ? Math.floor(m.depth * e) : 1,
                        c = 0,
                        u = 0,
                        h = 0
                    }
                    null !== i ? (d = i.x,
                    p = i.y,
                    f = i.z) : (d = 0,
                    p = 0,
                    f = 0);
                    const g = gt.convert(e.format)
                      , _ = gt.convert(e.type);
                    let v;
                    e.isData3DTexture ? (tt.setTexture3D(e, 0),
                    v = xt.TEXTURE_3D) : e.isDataArrayTexture || e.isCompressedArrayTexture ? (tt.setTexture2DArray(e, 0),
                    v = xt.TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY) : (tt.setTexture2D(e, 0),
                    v = xt.TEXTURE_2D),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_FLIP_Y_WEBGL, e.flipY),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_PREMULTIPLY_ALPHA_WEBGL, e.premultiplyAlpha),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_ALIGNMENT, e.unpackAlignment);
                    const x = xt.getParameter(xt.UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH)
                      , y = xt.getParameter(xt.UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT)
                      , S = xt.getParameter(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS)
                      , b = xt.getParameter(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS)
                      , M = xt.getParameter(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES);
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, m.width),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT, m.height),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS, c),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS, u),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES, h);
                    const E = t.isDataArrayTexture || t.isData3DTexture
                      , T = e.isDataArrayTexture || e.isData3DTexture;
                    if (t.isDepthTexture) {
                        const n = Q.get(t)
                          , i = Q.get(e)
                          , m = Q.get(n.__renderTarget)
                          , g = Q.get(i.__renderTarget);
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, m.__webglFramebuffer),
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, g.__webglFramebuffer);
                        for (let n = 0; n < l; n++)
                            E && (xt.framebufferTextureLayer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, Q.get(t).__webglTexture, r, h + n),
                            xt.framebufferTextureLayer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, Q.get(e).__webglTexture, a, f + n)),
                            xt.blitFramebuffer(c, u, s, o, d, p, s, o, xt.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT, xt.NEAREST);
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, null),
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, null)
                    } else if (0 !== r || t.isRenderTargetTexture || Q.has(t)) {
                        const n = Q.get(t)
                          , i = Q.get(e);
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, Ht),
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, Vt);
                        for (let t = 0; t < l; t++)
                            E ? xt.framebufferTextureLayer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, n.__webglTexture, r, h + t) : xt.framebufferTexture2D(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, xt.TEXTURE_2D, n.__webglTexture, r),
                            T ? xt.framebufferTextureLayer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, i.__webglTexture, a, f + t) : xt.framebufferTexture2D(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, xt.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, xt.TEXTURE_2D, i.__webglTexture, a),
                            0 !== r ? xt.blitFramebuffer(c, u, s, o, d, p, s, o, xt.COLOR_BUFFER_BIT, xt.NEAREST) : T ? xt.copyTexSubImage3D(v, a, d, p, f + t, c, u, s, o) : xt.copyTexSubImage2D(v, a, d, p, c, u, s, o);
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, null),
                        Z.bindFramebuffer(xt.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, null)
                    } else
                        T ? t.isDataTexture || t.isData3DTexture ? xt.texSubImage3D(v, a, d, p, f, s, o, l, g, _, m.data) : e.isCompressedArrayTexture ? xt.compressedTexSubImage3D(v, a, d, p, f, s, o, l, g, m.data) : xt.texSubImage3D(v, a, d, p, f, s, o, l, g, _, m) : t.isDataTexture ? xt.texSubImage2D(xt.TEXTURE_2D, a, d, p, s, o, g, _, m.data) : t.isCompressedTexture ? xt.compressedTexSubImage2D(xt.TEXTURE_2D, a, d, p, m.width, m.height, g, m.data) : xt.texSubImage2D(xt.TEXTURE_2D, a, d, p, s, o, g, _, m);
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, x),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT, y),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS, S),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS, b),
                    xt.pixelStorei(xt.UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES, M),
                    0 === a && e.generateMipmaps && xt.generateMipmap(v),
                    Z.unbindTexture()
                }

        class Kv {
            constructor() {
                this.$container = document.getElementById("Background"),
                this.setConfig(),
                this.scene = new ff,
                this.camera = new gf(-1,1,1,-1,.1,1e4),
                this.camera.position.set(0, 0, 10),
                this.renderer = new $v({
                    canvas: this.$container.querySelector("canvas"),
                    alpha: !0
                }),
                this.renderer.setSize(Bp.width, Bp.height),
                this.renderer.setPixelRatio(Bp.dpr)
            }
            setConfig() {
                const {width: t, height: e} = this.$container.getBoundingClientRect();
                Bp.dpr = Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 1.5),
                Bp.width = t,
                Bp.height = e,
                Bp.halfWidth = Bp.width / 2,
                Bp.halfHeight = Bp.height / 2,
                Bp.aspectRatio = Bp.width / Bp.height
            }
            resizeScene() {
                window.innerWidth >= window.innerHeight ? (this.camera.left = -1,
                this.camera.right = 1,
                this.camera.top = 1 / Bp.aspectRatio,
                this.camera.bottom = -1 / Bp.aspectRatio,
                Bp.sceneWidth = 2,
                Bp.sceneHeight = 2 / Bp.aspectRatio) : (this.camera.left = -1 * Bp.aspectRatio,
                this.camera.right = 1 * Bp.aspectRatio,
                this.camera.top = 1,
                this.camera.bottom = -1,
                Bp.sceneWidth = 2 * Bp.aspectRatio,
                Bp.sceneHeight = 2),
                this.camera.aspect = Bp.aspectRatio,
                this.camera.updateProjectionMatrix(),
                this.renderer.setSize(Bp.width, Bp.height)
            }
        }

            async switchPage(t) {

            showMessagesOnConsole() {
                console.log("%cNotice:", "font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;"),
                console.log("%cUnauthorized copying or reuse of the source code or content of this website is prohibited. These actions are a violation of copyright laws and may result in legal action. Please respect the intellectual property rights of the creators and refrain from using the code without permission. (Keita Yamada, p5aholic.me)", "font-size: 14px; line-height: 2;"),
                console.log("%cIf this message appears on a domain other than p5aholic.me, the site is using p5aholic.me's source code without permission and may be a copyright infringement. (Keita Yamada, p5aholic.me)", "font-size: 14px; line-height: 2;")
            }
        }
          , ax = new class {
            constructor() {}
            init() {
                window.Alpine = Yo,
                Yo.store("app", rx),
                Yo.start(),
                ix.init(),
                this.resizeMng = new Ki,
                this.resizeMng.setSizeFunc(( () => ({
                    width: window.innerWidth,
                    height: window.innerHeight
                }))),
                this.resize(),
                $i.add(this.update.bind(this))
            }
            resize() {
                const t = document.documentElement
                  , e = .01 * t.clientWidth
                  , n = .01 * t.clientHeight;
                document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--vw", `${e}px`),
                document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--vh", `${n}px`),
                document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--vmax", `${Math.max(e, n)}px`),
                document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--vmin", `${Math.min(e, n)}px`),
                ix.resize(),
                Yo.store("app").resize()
            }
            update(t) {
                this.resizeMng.check() && this.resize(),
                Yo.store("app").update(t),
                ix.update(t)
            }
        }
        ;
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", ( () => {
            "p5aholic.me" !== window.location.hostname && (window.location.href = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copyright_infringement"),
            function() {
                const t = document.querySelector('meta[name="viewport"]');
                function e() {
                    const e = window.outerWidth > 375 ? "width=device-width,initial-scale=1" : "width=375";
                    t.getAttribute("content") !== e && t.setAttribute("content", e)
                }
                window.addEventListener("resize", e),
                e()
            }(),
            ax.init()
        }
        ))
    }
    )()
}
)();
